For initializing a Repository use --> "git init"

For adding files to staging area:
    01_ "git add file.ext" --> adding one file
    02_ "git add file.ext file2.ext" --> adding multiple files
    03_ "git add *.ext" --> adding all files with this extension
    04_ "git add ."  --> adding all files

For Viewing the status:
    01_ "git status --> view full status
    02_ "git status -"s" --> view short status

For Committing the staging files:
    01_ "git commit -m 'Your message.'" --> one line message
    02_ "git commit" --> open editor to type a long message

For Skipping the staging area use --> "git commit -am 'Your message.'"

For Removing files:
    01_ "git rm file.ext" --> removes from working dir and staging area
    02_ "git rm --cached file.ext" --> removes from staging area only

For Renaming or Moving files use --> "git mv file.ext file2.ext"

For Viewing the staged or unstaged changes:
    01_ "git diff" --> view all unstaged changes
    02_ "git diff --staged" --> view all staged changes
    03_ "git diff --cached" --> view all staged changes

For Viewing the history:
    01_ "git log" --> view full histor
    02_ "git log --oneline" --> view short history
    03_ "git log --reverse" --> lists the commits from oldest to newest

For Viewing a commit:
    01_ "git show 921a2ff(unique identifier)"" --> view the given commit
    02_ "git show HEAD" --> view the last commit
    03_ "git show HEAD~2" --> two steps before the last commit
    04_ "git show HEAD:file.ext" --> view the version of file stored in last commit

To Undo git add command use this --> "git restore --staged file.ext"

For Discarding Local Changes:
    01_ "git restore file.ext" --> copies the file from index to working dir
    02_ "git restore file.ext file2.ext" --> restore multiple files
    03_ "git restore ." --> discard all local changes(except untracked file)
    04_ "git clean -fd" --> remove all untracked files

For restoring an earlier version of file use --> "git restore --source=HEAD~2 file.ext"
